            <q>the premises are, or have at any time been, the only or principal home of an individual".</q>
            I do not live in an Easton Neston, a Chatsworth or a house of that size, but I live in a house that is slightly too big for my needs and has been ever since I bought it.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0668P0-02177'>
